EXTRACTED VALUE: Sure the controls are a little clunky and the soundtrack is awkward, but Advanced Warfighter shines on the 360 with it's graphics.
It outguns just about every other console shooter currently on the market.
Multiplayer aside, this title is an outstanding display of next-gen gaming, and is easily the best Rainbow Six yet.
Party games don't come much better. The best of "Guitar Hero" and "SingStar" with drums. [July 2008, p.76]
